This chapter acknowledges a fundamental truth: while pure mathematics provides the laws, numerical methods provide the numbers. Every bridge that stands, every airplane that flies, every weather forecast that saves lives, every image on every screen—all rely on the algorithms described here. Numerical methods are the practical interface between mathematical theory and physical reality.

