Part Chapters Theme
Part 0 0-1 The Ground (axioms and infinity)
Part I 2-3 The Language (logic, sets, proof)
Part II 4-5 The Elements (numbers and arithmetic)
Part III 6-7 The Structures (algebra)
Part IV 8-9 The Stage (geometry and topology)
Part V 10-13 The Flow (analysis and differential equations)
Part VI 14-15 The Information (probability and discrete math)
Part VII 16 The Approximation (numerical methods)
Part VIII 17-18 The Bridge (constants and physics translation)

Dependencies

· Ch 0-3 are prerequisites for all subsequent chapters
· Ch 4 (Numbers) is required for Ch 5 (Arithmetic) and Ch 6-7 (Algebra)
· Ch 5 (Arithmetic) provides foundation for Ch 6 (Abstract Algebra)
· Ch 6-7 (Algebra) are needed for Ch 8-9 (Geometry/Topology) and Ch 18 (Physics)
· Ch 8 (Geometry) provides intuition for Ch 10-13 (Analysis)
· Ch 9 (Topology) provides foundation for Ch 10 (Real Analysis) and Ch 13 (Vector Calculus)
· Ch 10 (Real Analysis) is prerequisite for Ch 11 (Complex Analysis), Ch 12 (Diff Eqs), and Ch 13 (Vector Calculus)
· Ch 10-13 (Analysis) are needed for Ch 16 (Numerical Methods) and Ch 18 (Physics)
· Ch 14 (Probability) is needed for Ch 15 (Information Theory) and Ch 18 (Statistical Mechanics)
· Ch 15 (Discrete Math) stands somewhat independently but informs Ch 16 (Numerical Methods)
· Ch 16 (Numerical Methods) depends on most previous chapters
· Ch 17 (Constants) draws from throughout the volume
· Ch 18 (Physics Translation) integrates concepts from every part

